I didn't really know what she meant, but I know that a lot of people were scared to death at Ruby Daurus. I was, you know, I mean, it was just, you know, she was nice, but she was kind of like Ms. Baker.

01:38:27.000 --> 01:38:29.000
She did not suffer fools gladly.

01:38:29.000 --> 01:38:32.000
Was she still a spell on the student when you met her?

01:38:32.000 --> 01:38:39.000
No, she was totally off staff. She was full time in the office at that point. She had not yet married Cliff, and had not yet had the baby.

01:38:40.000 --> 01:38:46.000
But, and that was funny too. I remember we had a shower for Ruby when she was pregnant.

01:38:46.000 --> 01:38:56.000
And the thing is, you know, as an old female, right? And normally, I mean, people women know what to do at showers.

01:38:56.000 --> 01:39:07.000
You know, you have a little chichad and the baby, and there's always a, we were snakewomen. All our discussions always had to do with politics, and what was going on in the field, and who was doing what?

01:39:07.000 --> 01:39:23.000
And so I remember whole periods of silence. You know, it was like, okay, so how do we talk about this? You know, it's like the kind of informal, you know, it wasn't like we weren't friends. It wasn't like we didn't party. We knew how to party.

01:39:23.000 --> 01:39:36.000
But to have small talk, we didn't do small talk too well. So, and we didn't do baby stuff. You know, it's like, I mean, Julian was a family member, but you know, he had his kids and Alice was all over the place.

01:39:36.000 --> 01:39:45.000
Alice was off somewhere. She wasn't part of the staff. I'm trying to think minutes was married. I'm sure, but they were, you know, there were no babies.

01:39:45.000 --> 01:39:50.000
So, it was different when the men are married and have their families and women.

01:39:50.000 --> 01:39:57.000
Right. But also, I don't remember ever seeing Ruby's baby. I mean, I'm sure she brought it in at some point, but Cliff took care of the baby.

01:39:57.000 --> 01:40:03.000
You know, and she was away, but when she was away, when she came into that office, she was in the office.

01:40:03.000 --> 01:40:15.000
So, the shower was not, you know, she hadn't had the baby yet. And it was like, and none of the women that I remember had any babies. You know, nobody had any babies.

01:40:15.000 --> 01:40:24.000
You know, how could you have babies when you were on call 24 out of seven? You know, it was like, anyway, so I just remember the silences at the shower.

01:40:24.000 --> 01:40:41.000
So, anyway, Ruby, yeah, was, you know, she was just like a major force in that office. And she's saying, I need your reports, which is why I remember you're saying how interesting it was that you got, that there was so much documentation with SNCC.

01:40:42.000 --> 01:40:53.000
And that's because, you know, you had Ruby Darryl saying you got to write it down and you're not going to get, I mean, oftentimes we didn't get the little $9.64.

