I mean, that was a thankless job. I mean, it is thankless anyway within nonprofit, but we're, you know, it's the field staff say, I don't have to give you anything. You know, I'm putting my life on the line.

01:43:29.000 --> 01:43:35.000
Okay, so it's all that coming out. So I'm sitting there and I have.

01:43:35.000 --> 01:43:47.000
I remember letters to Michael, Mike standard, who was one of the lawyers in our pro, one of the many pro bono firms, our Benowitz and Boudin.

01:43:47.000 --> 01:43:56.000
And we had this, I mean, we had this chatty relationship. And part of it is, you know, all these people are making feel that, making me feel that I really belong to this thing.

01:43:56.000 --> 01:44:04.000
I mean, this is like this family of people. And so when I call Mike standard, it's like like attorney standard is, hey, Mike, how you doing? Did you do that?

01:44:04.000 --> 01:44:13.000
And I had these things, you know, I said something to him were to him or somebody where I said, and we could not do what we do. And it was in fun.

01:44:13.000 --> 01:44:22.000
I mean, and they knew I knew they would get we could not we hear in the South fighting for the there are freedom and our civil rights could not do what we do without you're doing what you did it.

