01:45:43.000 --> 01:45:57.000
Um, you know, it's like she's so captured me. She just lifted up. You know, she just she brought you to the place where you would go through hell to get your freedom.

01:45:57.000 --> 01:46:12.000
You know, she would follow her anywhere, you know, somebody said to to about Praetia that, you know, even Dr. King once said when both of them were at a out of mass meeting that he did not want to fall.

01:46:12.000 --> 01:46:26.000
He did not like following Praetia. Hi, Praes. Very high pray. And Praetia, you know, Praetia's parents were Pentecostal or evangelical, whatever ministers in a small black church in Philadelphia.

01:46:26.000 --> 01:46:36.000
So she came out of that. And then when she passed, she had just taken the Martin Luther King chair at Boston University.

01:46:36.000 --> 01:46:49.000
