01:46:49.000 --> 01:47:18.000
But, you know, really points her finger at some of the SCLC people who say to the folks after bloody Sunday. And there's and she talks about her that in her hands on the Freedom Plow section. She says, you know, I told the SCLC, Dr. King's organization, Southern Christian Leadership Conference, they had some of the field staff had said to the local people, you can't come on the demonstration unless you're philosophically nonviolent.

01:47:18.000 --> 01:47:32.000
Not just tactically, but philosophically nonviolent. And in fact, you are not really in the movement unless you can do this. And she said, I had to really get on their case because she said that was like blackmail.

01:47:32.000 --> 01:47:44.000
And she said, and it wasn't true. And you don't do that to people. You don't use the movement in that way. Now, she was philosophically nonviolent. But she understood that, you know, you separate that stuff, you know.

01:47:44.000 --> 01:48:01.000
But, you know, I remember, so I'm sitting there in the national office just typing a sub of tears pouring down. And I would, I would also transcribe, I would take the minutes for like executive committee meetings, executive committee meetings.

