foreign affairs officer from Kenya, may have had other things, but under, under, I think, Jomokanyata.

02:12:35.000 --> 02:12:38.000
And so, you know, this is newly independent Kenya.

02:12:38.000 --> 02:12:41.000
And so, he's this high ranking diplomat.

02:12:41.000 --> 02:12:46.000
And he's now in Atlanta. And Foreman finds out, because Foreman really kept aware, you know,

02:12:46.000 --> 02:12:55.000
was very much aware of the international relations part when it came to African affairs and, yeah, African affairs.

02:12:55.000 --> 02:13:02.000
So, he finds out Oginga Oginga is going to be star staying at the Peach Tree Manor,

02:13:02.000 --> 02:13:06.000
which it only a year before had been integrated.

02:13:06.000 --> 02:13:11.000
Because it was that whole thing about, you know, Atlanta, the city too busy to hate.

02:13:11.000 --> 02:13:17.000
And, you know, it had become really embarrassing for the federal government in this cold war,

02:13:17.000 --> 02:13:24.000
where, cold war time for these newly African nations to send diplomats into the South,

02:13:24.000 --> 02:13:31.000
and they couldn't eat at restaurants, right? Really bad, bad publicity,

02:13:31.000 --> 02:13:35.000
particularly because this was the time when Russia really was major.

02:13:35.000 --> 02:13:38.000
So, major force, it's the cold war.

02:13:38.000 --> 02:13:45.000
This country wants these newly independent African countries to go onto the side of the United States,

02:13:45.000 --> 02:13:47.000
and not on the side of Russia.

02:13:47.000 --> 02:13:52.000
So, how the U.S. looked with all of this horrible, you know, segregation and stuff,

02:13:52.000 --> 02:13:55.000
